+# Codex Writer Findings — PublicMenu Chain: publicmenu-260327-181015-2eb1
+## Findings
+1. [P2] Discounted price is still pre-rounded before `formatPrice` — `pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx` still wraps the discounted value with `Math.round(... * 100) / 100` in both `renderListCard` ([MenuView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L103)) and `renderTileCard` ([MenuView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L281)), and `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx` does the same in the detail drawer ([x.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3893)). This keeps the exact PM-119 bug active: the discounted price is formatted from a pre-rounded number instead of letting `formatPrice` handle precision consistently with the original price. FIX: replace those calls with `formatPrice(dish.price * (1 - partner.discount_percent / 100))` in `MenuView.jsx` and `formatPrice(detailDish.price * (1 - partner.discount_percent / 100))` in `x.jsx`, without changing the original price or discount badge logic.
+2. [P2] List-mode stepper is still below the 44px touch-target minimum — in `renderListCard`, the add button and both stepper buttons remain `w-9 h-9` at [MenuView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L156), [MenuView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L168), and [MenuView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L178), while the pill container is still `h-9 px-1` at [MenuView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L164). That leaves the list stepper at 36px instead of the required 44px and does not match the frozen tile-mode sizing. FIX: change only the list-mode classes to `w-11 h-11` for the three buttons and `h-11 px-1.5` for the pill container, with no layout or styling changes beyond those size classes.
+3. [P3] List-mode description is still clamped to one line — `renderListCard` keeps `line-clamp-1` at [MenuView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L96), so long dish descriptions still truncate after a single line. That means PM-147 is still unfixed in the list card. FIX: change that class to `line-clamp-2` on the list-card description only, leaving the tile-card description and dish-name clamp untouched.
+4. [P3] Detail drawer rating still renders as plain text without the star icon — `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx` still shows the rating block as raw spans at [x.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3911) through [x.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3915), so the drawer displays `4.8 (6)` instead of the same `DishRating` UI used in list/tile mode. The import section also still lacks `DishRating` near [x.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L94). FIX: add `import DishRating from "@/components/publicMenu/DishRating";` near the other public-menu imports and replace the raw rating block with `<DishRating avgRating={dishRatings[detailDish.id]?.avg} reviewCount={dishRatings[detailDish.id]?.count} />`, keeping the existing `Rating` import and section order unchanged.
+
+## Summary
+Total: 4 findings (0 P0, 0 P1, 2 P2, 2 P3)
+
